cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the network slice management function (NSMF) in 5G, which is related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a mathematical model for network slicing, which involves combinatorial designs and optimization algorithms, indicating a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses stability and utilization ratio functions, which are related to control and optimization, suggesting a possible fit with cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
